1. Go to the Anaconda Distribution page (https://www.anaconda.com/download).
2. Select the installer for your operating system (Windows, macOS, or Linux).
3. Choose the Python version you want to use (most users should choose the latest version).
4. Locate the downloaded .exe file and double-click it to run the installer
5. Follow the Installation Instructions

On Windows: Open the Anaconda Prompt from the Start Menu.
On macOS and Linux: Open the Terminal

Type:
1. conda create --name radiomics_env python=3.8
2. cd <path_to_project_directory>

Follow Instructions in 'Libraries' to install the required packages
